<TITLE> SC rejects govt petition against Khaleda bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 2 (bdnews24.com)The Supreme Court on Sunday rejected a government petition against opposition leader Khaleda Zia's bail in the Zia Orphanage Trust case. A full four-member Appellate Division bench, headed by the chief justice MM Ruhul Amin, dismissed the government's petition seeking leave to appeal against Khaleda's interim bail in the case that accuses her of embezzlement of the Trust's funds. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case with Ramna Police Station on July 3 last year. The High Court awarded Khaleda interim bail on August 26 last year. It also issued a rule ordering the government to explain why she should not be granted permanent bail in the case. Ruhul Amin's Appellate Division bench ordered the government on Sunday to reply to the High Court rule. bd
